  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good books on marketing?",
  "response": "There are many excellent books on marketing that cover a variety of topics, from foundational principles to advanced strategies. Here are some highly regarded titles:\n\n1. **\"Contagious: How to Build Word of Mouth in the Digital Age\" by Jonah Berger** - This book explores why certain ideas and products go viral and how to leverage this for your own marketing efforts.\n\n2. **\"Influence: The Psychology of Persuasion\" by Robert B. Cialdini** - A classic in the field, this book delves into the principles of persuasion and how they can be applied in marketing.\n\n3. **\"Building a StoryBrand: Clarify Your Message So Customers Will Listen\" by Donald Miller** - This book introduces the StoryBrand framework, which helps businesses clarify their message and create compelling brand narratives.\n\n4. **\"Positioning: The Battle for Your Mind\" by Al Ries and Jack Trout** - This seminal work on positioning explains how to establish a brand in the consumer's mind and differentiate it from competitors.\n\n5. **\"Made to Stick: Why Some Ideas Survive and Others Die\" by Chip Heath and Dan Heath** - This book investigates why some ideas are more memorable than others and provides practical advice for making your marketing messages \"stick.\"\n\n6. **\"This Is Marketing: You Can't Be Seen Until You Learn to See\" by Seth Godin** - Godin discusses the shift in marketing from mass marketing to a more focused, customer-centric approach.\n\n7. **\"The 22 Immutable Laws of Marketing\" by Al Ries and Jack Trout** - This book outlines fundamental marketing principles that can guide anybody looking to improve their marketing strategy.\n\n8. **\"Killing Marketing: How Innovative Businesses Are Turning Marketing Cost into Profit\" by Joe Pulizzi and Robert Rose** - This book discusses how traditional marketing practices are changing and how businesses can adapt to thrive in the new landscape.\n\n9. **\"The Lean Startup: How Today's Entrepreneurs Use Constant Innovation to Create Radically Successful Businesses\" by Eric Ries** - While primarily focused on startups, this book includes critical insights on marketing and product development.\n\n10. **\"Digital Marketing For Dummies\" by Ryan Deiss and Russ Henneberry** - A practical guide for anyone looking to understand and implement digital marketing strategies.\n\nThese books provide a mix of theory, practical advice, and insights into current marketing trends and should be valuable to both beginners and experienced marketers.",
